  "text": "The elucidation of the role of p38 MAPK in ischemiareperfusion has been limited by the lack of in vivo studies. To date, there has been only one in vivo study examining the role of p38 MAPK in acute pharmacological PC. Fryer et al. [CITATION_1] reported that opioid-mediated acute cardioprotection in an in vivo rat model was neither associated with p38 MAPK activation nor blocked by the p38 inhibitor SB-203580. The results of the present study, however, indicate that adenosine A 1 receptor acute PC is associated with preischemic activation of p38 MAPK in an in vivo rat model. The p38 MAPK inhibitor SB-203580 blocked both the cardioprotective effect of the adenosine agonist AMP-579 and the associated increase in preischemic p38 activity. These findings indicate that acute A 1 PC is mediated via a p38-dependent mechanism.",
